{"document_id": "3241690afef147279dec2be9b3929814__0", "text": "Referral REF-2024-1123 from St. John's Medical College Hospital / Dr. Priya Nair\nRe: Ananya Sharma, 20 / Female, District Bangalore\nReason: Persistent unexplained weight loss and intermittent fevers over the past three months, with recent onset of night sweats and fatigue. Initial workup at our facility suggests a complex hematological process requiring specialized oncological evaluation and management.\n\nPatient History:\nThe patient is a 20-year-old female homemaker, married, residing in Bangalore, Karnataka. She reports a history of being generally healthy until three months ago when she noticed a 5 kg weight loss despite no changes in diet or activity. She has experienced low-grade fevers in the evenings, drenching night sweats, and profound fatigue. She denies any recent travel, sick contacts, or specific dietary changes. Her family history is non-contributory for malignancy.\n\nClinical Examination:\nOn examination, the patient is pale, with a temperature of 37.8°C. She has generalized lymphadenopathy, most prominent in the cervical and axillary regions. Abdominal examination reveals mild hepatosplenomegaly. No focal neurological deficits were noted.\n\nInvestigations:\nComplete blood count shows pancytopenia with hemoglobin of 8.5 g/dL, total leukocyte count of 2.1 x 10^9/L, and platelet count of 85 x 10^9/L. Peripheral smear reveals atypical lymphocytes. Serum LDH is elevated at 450 U/L. A chest X-ray is clear. An abdominal ultrasound shows mild hepatosplenomegaly.\n\nReferral Details:\nWe request a comprehensive hematological and oncological assessment to establish a definitive diagnosis and initiate appropriate treatment. The patient's MRN-2024-0815-001 is attached for your records. Please contact the patient or her next of kin, her father Rakesh Sharma, at 9876543210 for any further information. Her P8765432 and KA01 2020 0001234 are available for identification purposes. We look forward to your expert opinion and collaborative care.", "tokenized_text": ["Referral", "REF", "-", "2024", "-", "1123", "from", "St", ".", "John's", "Medical", "College", "Hospital", "/", "Dr", ".", "Priya", "Nair", "Re", ":", "Ananya", "Sharma", ",", "20", "/", "Female", ",", "District", "Bangalore", "Reason", ":", "Persistent", "unexplained", "weight", "loss", "and", "intermittent", "fevers", "over", "the", "past", "three", "months", ",", "with", "recent", "onset", "of", "night", "sweats", "and", "fatigue", ".", "Initial", "workup", "at", "our", "facility", "suggests", "a", "complex", "hematological", "process", "requiring", "specialized", "oncological", "evaluation", "and", "management", ".", "Patient", "History", ":", "The", "patient", "is", "a", "20", "-", "year", "-", "old", "female", "homemaker", ",", "married", ",", "residing", "in", "Bangalore", ",", "Karnataka", ".", "She", "reports", "a", "history", "of", "being", "generally", "healthy", "until", "three", "months", "ago", "when", "she", "noticed", "a", "5", "kg", "weight", "loss", "despite", "no", "changes", "in", "diet", "or", "activity", ".", "She", "has", "experienced", "low", "-", "grade", "fevers", "in", "the", "evenings", ",", "drenching", "night", "sweats", ",", "and", "profound", "fatigue", ".", "She", "denies", "any", "recent", "travel", ",", "sick", "contacts", ",", "or", "specific", "dietary", "changes", ".", "Her", "family", "history", "is", "non", "-", "contributory", "for", "malignancy", ".", "Clinical", "Examination", ":", "On", "examination", ",", "the", "patient", "is", "pale", ",", "with", "a", "temperature", "of", "37.8", "°", "C", ".", "She", "has", "generalized", "lymphadenopathy", ",", "most", "prominent", "in", "the", "cervical", "and", "axillary", "regions", ".", "Abdominal", "examination", "reveals", "mild", "hepatosplenomegaly", ".", "No", "focal", "neurological", "deficits", "were", "noted", ".", "Investigations", ":", "Complete", "blood", "count", "shows", "pancytopenia", "with", "hemo